1.title: Xcalak and Banco Chinchorro, Mexico
1.plot: Wreck Diving Magazine travels to Xcalak and the uninhabited Banco Chinchorro, Mexico to dive on some of the many shipwrecks that foundered on the atoll.

2.title: Iraq - Winged Bull
2.plot: Award winning Wreck Diving Magazine goes to Iraq in search of a large winged bull, sculpted of limestone in 721-705 BC, and lost in the Tigris River in the mid-1800s.

1.title: Episode #1.1
1.plot: Episode 1. Award winning Wreck Diving Magazine goes to Key West to dive on The Atocha, a Spanish galleon sunk in the 1600's, go behind the scenes at Mel Fisher's Treasures museum, and check out the Aquascan DX200 magnetometer.

1.title: Aquarium Shark Dive!
1.plot: Wreck Diving Magazine publisher Joe Porter's first dive ever with sharks, in the North Carolina Aquarium on Roanoke Island, Outer Banks.

imdb.plot outline: Award-winning Wreck Diving Magazine presents Wreck Diving Magazine TV. Episode 1: Wreck Diving Magazine goes to Key West to dive on The Atocha, a Spanish galleon sunk in the 1600's, go behind the scenes at Mel Fisher's Treasures museum, and check out the Aquascan DX200 magnetometer. Episode 2 - Aquarium Shark Dive: A great dive in the NC Aquarium on Roanoke Island, Outer Banks. Joe's first dive ever with sharks. Episode 3 - Xcalak and Banco Chinchorro, MX: Wreck Diving Magazine goes to Xcalak and the uninhabited Banco Chinchorro, Mexico to dive on some of the many shipwrecks that foundered on the atoll. Episode 4 - Iraq - Winged Bull. Wreck Diving Magazine goes to Basra, Iraq in search of a 60-ton winged bull sculpted in 721-705 BC, and lost in the mid-1800s.
